LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA
ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SESSION
LEGISLATIVE BILL 70
FINAL READING
Introduced by DeBoer, 10; Raybould, 28; Conrad, 46.
Read first time January 09, 2025
Committee: Judiciary
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to children and families; to amend sections
2 43-104.15, 43-107, 43-512.04, 43-1402, 43-1404, 43-1405, and
3 43-1410, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, sections 43-101,
4 43-101.01, 43-102, 43-104, 43-104.08, 43-104.13, and 43-2924,
5 Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement, 2024, and section 43-1401,
6 Revised Statutes Supplement, 2025; to provide for adoption by a
7 second adult person; to define and redefine terms; to change
8 provisions relating to consent to adoption, home studies,
9 terminology, child support and medical support, and the
10 applicability of the Parenting Act; to eliminate obsolete
11 provisions; to harmonize provisions; and to repeal the original
12 sections.
13 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
