2 2024, is amended to read:
3 43-101 (1) Subject to sections 43-101 to 43-115 and except Except as
4 otherwise provided in the Nebraska Indian Child Welfare Act and
5 subsections (4) and (5) of this section: ,
6 (a) Any any minor child may be adopted by any adult person or
7 persons;
8 (b) Any minor and any adult child may be adopted by the spouse of
9 such child's parent; and
10 (c) Any minor child who has a sole legal parent may be adopted by a
11 second adult person if:
12 (i) The sole legal parent consents as provided in section 43-104;
13 (ii) The child has a parent-child relationship with the second adult
14 person;
15 (iii) The child is the biological child of the second adult person;
16 (iv) The second adult person has not previously had such person's
17 parental rights to such child terminated; and
18 (v) An adoptive home study is completed as provided in section
19 43-107.
20 (2) Subject to sections 43-101 to 43-115 and except as otherwise
21 provided in subsections (4) and (5) of this section:
22 (a) Any adult child may be adopted by the spouse of such adult
23 child's parent; and
24 in the cases and subject to sections 43-101 to 43-115, except that
25 no person having a spouse may adopt a minor child unless the spouse joins
26 in the petition therefor. If the spouse so joins in the petition
27 therefor, the adoption shall be by them jointly, except that an adult
28 spouse may adopt a child of the other spouse whether born in or out of
29 wedlock.
30 (2) Any adult child may be adopted by any person or persons subject
31 to sections 43-101 to 43-115, except that no person having a spouse may
