5 are not the stepparent of the adult child may be permitted if the adult
6 child has had a parent-child relationship with the prospective parent or
7 parents for a period of at least six months next preceding the adult
8 child's age of majority and:
9 (i) The (a) the adult child has no living parents; ,
10 (ii) The (b) the adult child's parent or parents had been deprived
11 of parental rights to such child by the order of any court of competent
12 jurisdiction; ,
13 (iii) The (c) the parent or parents, if living, have relinquished
14 the adult child for adoption by a written instrument; ,
15 (iv) The (d) the parent or parents had abandoned the child for at
16 least six months next preceding the adult child's age of majority or for
17 a substantial portion of the time since the adult child reached the age
18 of majority; , or
19 (v) The (e) the parent or parents are incapable of consenting; or .
20 (vi) The adult child has a sole legal parent who consents as
21 provided in section 43-104.
22 (3) The substitute consent provisions of section 43-105 do not apply
23 to adoptions under this subsection (2) of this section.
24 (4) No person with a spouse may adopt a minor child or an adult
25 child unless the spouse of such person joins in the petition for
26 adoption, in which case the adoption shall be made by such persons
27 jointly.
28 (5) An adoption shall not be permitted under this section if it
29 would result in a minor or adult child having more than two legal
30 parents.
