1 2024, is amended to read:
2 43-101.01 For purposes of sections 43-101 to 43-115:
3 (1) Acknowledged father means an individual who has:
4 (a) Executed a valid acknowledgment of paternity; or
5 (b) Acknowledged paternity through establishment of a familial
6 relationship with the child for a period of at least six months;
7 (2) Adjudicated father means an individual who has been determined
8 by a court of competent jurisdiction, in this state or in another state
9 or territory of the United States, to be the biological or legal father
10 of a minor child; and
11 (3) Juvenile court means the separate juvenile court where it has
12 been established pursuant to sections 43-2,111 to 43-2,127 and the county
13 court sitting as a juvenile court in all other counties; and .
14 (4) Sole legal parent means a legal parent of a child with respect
15 to whom no other person has parental rights.
